notes: estimate - aquatic larvae, adults overwinter, produce next generation and die in May, must overwinter as adult for successful reproduction
3-5 week adult reproductive diapause after eclosion, overwinter as first instar (365/4)
eggs Nov, hatched May, 29 day pupation, 197 days adult life
overwinters as second instar or pupa

source: Stokes et al., 1991; Courard-Hauri et al., 2006
